There is **no difference** between **`.yml`** and **`.yaml`** files in terms of content, syntax, or how they work. Both are used for **YAML (YAML Ainâ€™t Markup Language)**.

The only difference is the **file extension**:

* **`.yaml`** â†’ The official recommended extension (preferred by YAML maintainers).
* **`.yml`** â†’ A shorter alternative extension, often used historically because some older systems limited file extensions to 3 characters.

